{"article_id":"F0TZDbr1LSA3W9aX","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The White House and congressional leaders continue to talk about taxes , spending cuts and how to avoid the so-called fiscal cliff","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"that arrives at midnight Dec. 31 -","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"when Bush-era tax cuts are set to expire","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"and automatic spending cuts are set to go into effect .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"As NPR and others cover the story ,","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"we 'll try to to point to interesting reports and analyses .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Here are three of the latest .","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"-- `` Obama To GOP :","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"I 'm Done Negotiating With Myself , '' by Ezra Klein on The Washington Post 's Wonkblog .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Klein writes","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"that :","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"`` We 're seeing two things here .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"One is that the negotiations are n't going well .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"When one side begins leaking the other side 's proposals ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"that 's typically a bad sign .","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"The other is that Republicans are frustrated at the new Obama","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"they 're facing :","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"The Obama","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"who refuses to negotiate with himself .","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"`` That 's what you 're really seeing in this 'proposal . '","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Previously , Obama 's pattern had been to offer plans","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"that roughly tracked","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"where he thought","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"the compromise should end up .","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"The White House 's belief was that","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"by being solicitous in their policy proposals ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"they would win goodwill on the other side ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"even if they did n't ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"the media would side with them ,","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"realizing","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"they 'd sought compromise","depth":15},{"id":32,"text":"and been rebuffed .","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"They do n't believe that anymore . ''","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"-- `` McConnell 'Burst Into Laughter '","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"as Geithner Outlined Obama 's Plan , ''","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"by Fred Barnes for The Weekly Standard .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"He reports","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that :","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"`` Mitch McConnell , the Senate Republican leader , says","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"he 'burst into laughter ' Thursday","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"when Treasury Secretary Tim Geithner outlined the administration proposal","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"for averting the fiscal cliff .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"He was n't trying to embarrass Geithner ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"McConnell says ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"only responding candidly to his one-sided plan , explicit on tax increases , vague on spending cuts . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"-- `` How Much Income Taxes Could Rise :","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"A Breakdown Of The Options , '' by NPR 's John Ydstie on our It 's All Politics blog .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"In the negotiations , John writes :","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"`` Perhaps the most important sticking point is over income tax rates .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"The outcome of the negotiations will determine how many Americans will face higher tax rates","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"- and how much of a hike it will be . ''","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":103,"left":55,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":55,"left":0,"right":54,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":54,"left":1,"right":53,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":53,"left":2,"right